@startuml Wissenstest_06_Architektur_Gesamt
!theme plain
skinparam classBackgroundColor #F0F0F0
skinparam classBorderColor #333333
skinparam classArrowColor #333333
skinparam fontSize 12
skinparam linetype ortho

title Wissenstest - Klassendiagramm Teil 6: Gesamt-Architektur und Komponenten-Übersicht

' ==================== ARCHITECTURE LAYERS ====================

package "1. Presentation Layer (Client)" {
  component [Web Browser] as WebBrowser
  
  note left of WebBrowser
    - HTML5 / CSS3
    - Vanilla JavaScript
    - Responsive Design
    - HTTP Communication
  end note
}

package "2. Web Layer (Request Handler)" {
  component [AuthServlet] as AuthServlet
  component [TestServlet] as TestServlet
  component [AdminServlet] as AdminServlet
  component [QuestionServlet] as QuestionServlet
  component [ProgressionServlet] as ProgressionServlet
  component [FilterAuthenticator] as FilterAuth
  
  note right of AuthServlet
    HTTP POST/GET Handling
    Session Management
  end note
}

package "3. Business Logic Layer (Services)" {
  component [AuthService] as AuthService
  component [TestService] as TestService
  component [ProgressionService] as ProgressionService
  component [AdminService] as AdminService
  
  note bottom of TestService
    CRUD, Test-Execution
    Complex Business Logic
  end note
}

package "4. Data Access Layer (DAO)" {
  component [JdbcUserDao] as UserDAO
  component [JdbcQuestionDao] as QuestionDAO
  component [JdbcAnswerDao] as AnswerDAO
  component [JdbcClozeTokenDao] as ClozeDAO
  component [JdbcTestDao] as TestDAO
  component [JdbcAttemptDao] as AttemptDAO
  component [QuestionRepository] as QRepo
  
  note right of UserDAO
    PreparedStatements
    ResultSet Mapping
  end note
}

package "5. Data Layer (Database)" {
  database "PostgreSQL\n(Port 5433)" as PostgreSQL
  
  note right of PostgreSQL
    - users, questions, tests
    - attempts, answers
    - cloze_tokens, etc.
  end note
}

package "6. Utility & Infrastructure" {
  component [DbConnectionManager] as DBConnMgr
  component [PasswordUtils] as PwdUtils
  component [Logger] as Log
  component [ValidationUtils] as ValUtils
  component [ExceptionHandler] as ExcHandler
  component [ConfigManager] as ConfigMgr
  
  note bottom of DBConnMgr
    HikariCP Connection Pool
    Singleton Pattern
  end note
}

' ==================== REQUEST FLOW ====================

WebBrowser -->|HTTP| FilterAuth : Request
FilterAuth -->|Check Session| AuthService : Authenticate
AuthService -->|User Data| WebBrowser : Response (JSP Rendered)

WebBrowser -->|Test Actions| TestServlet : POST/GET
TestServlet -->|Business Logic| TestService : Call
TestService -->|Data Access| QuestionDAO : Query
QuestionDAO -->|JDBC| DBConnMgr : Connection
DBConnMgr -->|SQL| PostgreSQL : Execute
PostgreSQL -->|ResultSet| QuestionDAO : Return
QuestionDAO -->|Mapped Objects| TestService : Return
TestService -->|Score Calc| ProgressionService : Evaluate
ProgressionService -->|Store Result| AttemptDAO : Save
AttemptDAO -->|JDBC| PostgreSQL : Insert
PostgreSQL -->|Success| AttemptDAO : Confirm
AttemptDAO -->|Object| ProgressionService : Attempt
ProgressionService -->|Statistics| TestServlet : Return
TestServlet -->|JSP Rendering| WebBrowser : Result Page

' ==================== UTILITY USAGE ====================

AuthService -.->|Hash/Verify| PwdUtils : Security
TestService -.->|Validate| ValUtils : Input Check
ProgressionService -.->|Log Events| Log : Logging
DBConnMgr -.->|Load Config| ConfigMgr : Configuration
all -.->|Exception Handling| ExcHandler : Error Management

' ==================== DATA MODELS ====================
note right of PostgreSQL
  **Primary Model Classes:**
  
  - User (id, username, password_hash, role)
  - Question (id, text, type, difficulty)
  - Test (id, title, questions)
  - Attempt (id, user_id, test_id, score, grade)
  - AttemptAnswer (attempt_id, question_id, answer)
  
  **Supporting Tables:**
  - AnswerOption (for MC questions)
  - ClozeToken (for Fill-in-the-blank)
  - TestQuestions (N:M relation)
  
  **Indices:** 
  - On Foreign Keys
  - On type, difficulty
  - On created_at for pagination
end note

' ==================== SECURITY MEASURES ====================
note bottom of FilterAuth
  **Security Layers:**
  
  1. Session Authentication
     - HttpSession Management
     - Timeout handling
  
  2. Authorization
     - Role-based Access Control (RBAC)
     - Admin-only endpoints
  
  3. Password Security
     - SHA-256 Hashing
     - Salt generation
  
  4. SQL Injection Prevention
     - PreparedStatements
     - Parameter binding
  
  5. Input Validation
     - Client + Server-side
     - XSS prevention
end note

' ==================== DEPLOYMENT ====================
note bottom
  **Deployment Stack:**
  
  - Java 17 (Runtime)
  - Apache Tomcat 9.0.85 (App Server)
  - PostgreSQL 16 (Database)
  - Maven 3.9.6 (Build Tool)
  - HikariCP 5.1 (Connection Pool)
  
  **Startup Script:** start_project.ps1
  - Automated tool setup
  - Database initialization
  - Tomcat deployment
end note

' ==================== LEGEND ====================
note left of WebBrowser
  **Legend:**
  
  → Synchrone Calls
  ..→ Utility Calls
  | HTTP Communication
  [SQL] Database Access
end note

@enduml
